# SDLC (opt-in)

Invoke manually (`@sdlc`) or when unsure which workflow to use. **Do not treat this as always-on process.**

## Pick a path

| Situation | What to run |
|-----------|-------------|
| **Build / implement / fix end-to-end** | **`ship-feature` skill** ‚Äî full wave loop (grill ‚Üí research ‚Üí code‚à•test ‚Üí validate‚à•guard ‚Üí comment‚à•review ‚Üí memory) |
| Quick fix, 1‚Äì2 files, clear scope | Graph scout (see `main.mdc`) ‚Üí implement. Skip ship-feature. |
| Touching a **god node** | Graph scout + drill **before** editing |
| Need a written spec doc | gstack `/spec` *(optional ‚Äî `INSTALL_GSTACK=1 bash setup`)* |
| Browser / deploy QA | gstack `/qa`, `/ship` *(optional)* |

---

## ship-feature (primary)

Use when the user says *build this*, *implement X*, *add feature*, *fix and ship*, or any end-to-end request.

**Rules:**
- **Wave 0 (grill) finishes before any sub-agent** ‚Äî one question at a time, with your recommended answer.
- **One sub-agent per Task** ‚Äî parallel agents only within the same wave, in a single message.
- **Wave 5 memory** ‚Äî parent writes session notes; memory-graph hook also updates `memory/state.yaml` on stop.

Full wave prompts ‚Üí `.agents/skills/ship-feature/SKILL.md`

---

## memory-graph integration

| After work | Where it goes |
|------------|---------------|
| Open threads, one-line state | `context:` / `open:` in today's `sessions/*.md` |
| Rolled-up working memory | `memory/state.yaml` *(auto, every file-changing stop)* |
| God nodes touched | Session frontmatter + graph scout summary |

No hook followup for session capture. No prose *Decisions* essays ‚Äî git diff is *what*; memory is *what's still open*.

**Before starting a feature:** read `memory/state.yaml` + scan `memory.md`.

---

## Graph

Never load `graphify-out/graph.json` into parent chat. Scout subagent ‚Üí optional drill if HIGH/CRITICAL. See `main.mdc` and `graph-scout` skill.

